This paper briefly describes a graduate-level education program in telecommunications jointly developed and managed by Pace University and IBM Corporation. The program is mainly designed to provide IBM employees with improved technical and managerial knowledge and skills in telecommunications. The paper, however, focuses on how the university also is serving as a facilitator of intracorporate cooperation and team building by providing a comfortable academic environment. This encourages the exchange of ideas, the sharing of perspectives, and the forming of an “affinity” group of telecommunications professionals that runs across lines of specialization. Now that over 90 students have graduated from the program, the authors argue that the company’s internal telecommunications organization is in a better state of readiness to adjust to new roles, technologies, and organizational restructuring so that new business opportunities may be successfully realized. THE STRATEGIC USE OF INFORMATION